{# ============================================================
   Customer-Support Intent Detection — prompt template
   One template renders zero-shot / few-shot / JSON / clarify variants.
   Variables:
     - intents        : list of {name, description}
     - message        : the customer message to classify
     - examples       : optional list of {message, intent}  (few-shot)
     - want_json      : bool  -> request structured JSON output
     - allow_clarify  : bool  -> permit a clarifying follow-up question
     - want_confidence: bool  -> ask for a confidence score
   ============================================================ #}
You are an expert customer-support assistant. Classify the customer's message
into exactly one of the following intents.

Candidate intents:
{% for intent in intents %}
  - {{ intent.name }}: {{ intent.description }}
{% endfor %}
{% if examples %}

Here are some labeled examples:
{% for ex in examples %}
Message: "{{ ex.message }}"
Intent: {{ ex.intent }}
{% endfor %}
{% endif %}
{% if allow_clarify %}

If the message is too ambiguous to classify confidently, respond instead with a
single short clarifying question to the customer.
{% endif %}

Now classify this message:
Message: "{{ message }}"
{% if want_json %}

Respond ONLY with a JSON object using this schema and no extra text:
{"intent": "<one_of_the_intent_names>"{% if want_confidence %}, "confidence": <float 0-1>{% endif %}}
{% else %}

Respond with the single intent name{% if want_confidence %}, followed by a confidence score between 0 and 1{% endif %}.
{% endif %}
